773
00:39:56,688 --> 00:39:58,668
that the player was having difficulty understanding

774
00:39:59,328 --> 00:40:02,009
what resource was going to be used for what.

775
00:40:02,589 --> 00:40:04,929
It's really difficult to judge a value of something

776
00:40:04,969 --> 00:40:07,270
when you have 80 different resources in your inventory

777
00:40:07,290 --> 00:40:08,870
and they all look slightly the same.

778
00:40:10,797 --> 00:40:13,659
Plus the reverse of that problem also started happening.

779
00:40:14,279 --> 00:40:16,941
We have merchants in the world where you can go to,

780
00:40:17,401 --> 00:40:19,683
traders, sorry, traders in the world that you can go to

781
00:40:20,223 --> 00:40:24,766
and you can get them to craft your own new weapons

782
00:40:25,247 --> 00:40:26,948
and you need to bring specific resources for that.

783
00:40:27,448 --> 00:40:29,269
But players were starting to ask questions like,

784
00:40:29,309 --> 00:40:30,650
okay, so that's a cool resource,

785
00:40:30,690 --> 00:40:32,211
but where the hell do I get that?

786
00:40:33,032 --> 00:40:34,813
So those kind of problems started rearing their head.

787
00:40:38,189 --> 00:40:42,973
Now, one of our intentions that made this problem even worse

788
00:40:43,493 --> 00:40:46,316
was that we wanted the tribes to be primitive.

789
00:40:47,341 --> 00:40:51,203
So they wouldn't understand what a CPU is.

790
00:40:51,323 --> 00:40:54,425
They wouldn't know what a camera lens is.

791
00:40:54,686 --> 00:40:57,007
So they just call things as they see them.

792
00:40:57,507 --> 00:40:58,788
A lens becomes an eye.

793
00:41:00,409 --> 00:41:03,371
A battery, it looks like a coil, so let's call it a coil.

794
00:41:03,771 --> 00:41:06,993
And they know that if they shoot the middle bit of the

795
00:41:07,033 --> 00:41:09,375
robot and then it kills, well, that's probably its heart.

796
00:41:10,415 --> 00:41:12,977
So we created, essentially, a difference between the world

797
00:41:13,017 --> 00:41:14,278
language and the player language.

798
00:41:14,942 --> 00:41:18,428
And this abstraction layer also added to the confusion.

799
00:41:19,470 --> 00:41:22,315
Players could not understand the value of something

800
00:41:22,415 --> 00:41:25,441
due to this ambiguity as well.

801
00:41:27,733 --> 00:41:32,317
So we were already very far into production

802
00:41:32,357 --> 00:41:34,278
when we started realizing we had these problems.

803
00:41:34,758 --> 00:41:37,440
And it was truly too late to really change

804
00:41:37,460 --> 00:41:38,841
the entire economy at this stage.

805
00:41:39,662 --> 00:41:41,884
So instead, we focused on adding tools

806
00:41:41,984 --> 00:41:43,425
to mitigate those problems.

807
00:41:44,365 --> 00:41:47,347
An example would be the trader jobs that you added.

808
00:41:47,367 --> 00:41:50,770
Now, raise of hands, who here has made

809
00:41:50,970 --> 00:41:52,971
